1
00:00:07,920 --> 00:00:09,240
(STREET LIGHT BUZZING)

2
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:14,840
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

3
00:00:19,120 --> 00:00:20,160
(SIGHS)

4
00:00:20,240 --> 00:00:21,560
(CASH REGISTER BEEPING)

5
00:00:22,440 --> 00:00:24,480
Better cash up, then.

6
00:00:24,560 --> 00:00:26,760
I suppose John Joe can just wait for me.

7
00:00:26,840 --> 00:00:28,720
No, I'll do it. You head off.

8
00:00:29,160 --> 00:00:30,400
(ELECTRICITY BUZZING)

9
00:00:32,680 --> 00:00:34,800
When's the council going to fix this?

10
00:00:34,880 --> 00:00:37,080
Last night, my telly went off
in the middle of 7op Model.

11
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:39,440
John Joe's waiting.
I'll do the changing rooms, too.

12
00:00:39,520 --> 00:00:41,200
Oh, thanks, Shona.

13
00:00:44,720 --> 00:00:46,080
There's a list on the fridge.

14
00:00:46,160 --> 00:00:47,240
I saw it.

15
00:00:47,320 --> 00:00:49,960
And I've labelled the food
and sort of numbered it.

16
00:00:50,040 --> 00:00:52,600
Sophie, you don't need to number food.

17
00:00:52,680 --> 00:00:55,320
It's just a suggestion.
Also, my mum might phone.

18
00:00:55,400 --> 00:00:58,080
-Might?
-And your mum and my dad.

19
00:00:58,160 --> 00:01:00,240
And, you know, just innocent people.

20
00:01:00,320 --> 00:01:02,240
I can cope on my own.

21
00:01:02,320 --> 00:01:04,440
Now, please go and have a rest.
You need it.

22
00:01:04,520 --> 00:01:06,280
-I love you.
-I love you, too.

23
00:01:06,360 --> 00:01:07,680
And thank you for this.

24
00:01:08,240 --> 00:01:10,160
And I do know you can cope on your own.

25
00:01:10,240 --> 00:01:12,880
And I may have drawn some arrows
in the fridge.

26
00:01:12,960 --> 00:01:14,520
Okay, you really have to go now.

27
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:22,080
(SIGHS) Oh, Kelly!

28
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:25,320
(CLATTERING)

29
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,640
Hello? Sorry, we need to close up.

30
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:33,000
Two minutes, okay?

31
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:37,200
Mum, it's not just you.
I'm phoning everybody.

32
00:01:37,480 --> 00:01:41,120
I'm texting the world,
"Craig Owens can do it on his own."

33
00:01:41,520 --> 00:01:43,320
No one is coming to help me.

34
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:44,520
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

35
00:01:45,520 --> 00:01:47,160
Mum, I'm going to have to call you back.

36
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:48,280
(KNOCKING CONTINUES)

37
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:50,680
I'm coping. I'm coping on my own.

38
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:52,400
I'm coping on my own!

39
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:54,840
I'm coping on my own!

40
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:57,360
Hello, Craig. I'm back!

41
00:01:58,440 --> 00:01:59,520
She didn't...

42
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:00,960
How could she phone you?

43
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:03,520
How could who phone me?
Nobody phoned me. I'm just here.

44
00:02:03,600 --> 00:02:06,640
Oh, you've redecorated!
I don't like it.

45
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:08,800
It's a different house. We moved.

46
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:10,240
Yes, that's it.

47
00:02:10,640 --> 00:02:12,040
Doctor, what are you doing here?

48
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:14,920
Social call. Thought it was about time
I tried one out.

49
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,800
How are you?

50
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:18,920
I'm fine.

51
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,160
This is the bit where I say
I'm fine, too, isn't it?

52
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:22,880
I'm fine, too.

53
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:25,440
-Good.
-Love to Sophie. Bye.

54
00:02:26,920 --> 00:02:28,240
(ELECTRICITY BUZZING)

55
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:29,600
Something's wrong.

56
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:35,600
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER HUMMING)

57
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:36,960
On your own, you said.

58
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:38,120
But you're not.

59
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:40,120
You're not on your own.

60
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:41,840
Just... Shh.

61
00:02:41,920 --> 00:02:44,240
Increased sulphur emissions.
And look at the state of this place.

62
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:46,760
-What are you not telling me?
-Doctor, please.

63
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,080
-Shh.
-No, you shush.

64
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:49,480
-Shh!
-No, you shush!

65
00:02:50,320 --> 00:02:51,400
Doctor...

66
00:03:00,160 --> 00:03:01,280
Hello?

67
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:02,440
Who's in there?

68
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:07,640
Whoever you are, get off this planet.

69
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:08,880
(BABY CRYING)

70
00:03:08,960 --> 00:03:10,400
You've woken him!

71
00:03:10,920 --> 00:03:12,200
(CRAIG SIGHING)

72
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:14,640
Hello?

73
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:16,320
Are you all right?

74
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:22,360
(SCREAMING)

75
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:25,240
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

76
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,840
So, when you say on your own...

77
00:03:59,920 --> 00:04:02,040
Yes, I meant on my own
with the baby, yes.

78
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:05,160
Because no one thinks I can cope
on my own, which is so unfair.

79
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:07,480
Because I can't cope on my own with him.

80
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:10,240
I can't. He just cries all the time.

81
00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:12,360
I mean, do they have off switches?

82
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:14,280
Human beings? No.
Believe me, I've checked.

83
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,680
No, babies!

84
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:18,080
Same difference.
Sometimes this works, though.

85
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:20,080
Shh.

86
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:26,120
-Can you teach me to do that?
-Probably not.

87
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:29,160
Oh, please. Come on. I need something.
I am rubbish at this.

88
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:31,360
-At what?
-Being a dad.

89
00:04:31,440 --> 00:04:33,920
You read all the books and they tell you
you'll know what to do

90
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:37,360
if you follow your instincts.
I have no instincts.

91
00:04:37,560 --> 00:04:39,000
That's what this weekend's about,

92
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:42,200
trying to prove to people
I can do this one thing well.

93
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:43,840
(LAUGHING)

94
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:48,240
So what did you call him? Will I blush?

95
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:50,280
No, we didn't call him The Doctor.

96
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:52,160
No, I didn't think you would.

97
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:54,960
He's called Alfie.
What are you doing here, anyway?

98
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,400
Yes, he likes that, Alfie,

99
00:04:56,480 --> 00:05:00,400
though personally he prefers to be
called Stormageddon, Dark Lord of AIL

100
00:05:00,520 --> 00:05:02,840
-I'm sorry, what?
-That's what he calls himself.

101
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:04,560
And how do you know that?

102
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:05,800
I speak baby.

103
00:05:06,440 --> 00:05:07,640
Of course you do.

104
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:09,440
I don't even know
when his nappy needs changing,

105
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:11,320
I'm the one
who's supposed to be his dad.

106
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:12,840
Oh, God.

107
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:16,240
Yeah, I'm wondering where his mum is.
Where is Sophie?

108
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:19,000
She's gone away with Melina
for the weekend. She needs a rest.

109
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:20,280
(COOING)

110
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:23,440
No, he's your dad.
You can't just call him Not Mum.

111
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:25,160
-"Not Mum"?
-That's you.

112
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:28,400
Also Not Mum, that's me.
And everybody else is...

113
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:30,400
-(BURBLING)
-Peasants.

114
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:32,000
That's a bit unfortunate.

115
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:35,440
What are you here for? What's happening?

116
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:37,400
-Just popped in to say hello.
-You don't do that.

117
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:39,640
I checked upstairs when we moved in.
It's real.

118
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:41,840
And next door, both sides,
they're humans.

119
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:44,120
Is it the fridge?
Are there aliens in my fridge?

120
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:46,920
I just want to see you, Craig.
Cross my hearts.

121
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:48,160
Been knocking around on my own
for a bit,

122
00:05:48,240 --> 00:05:49,800
bit of a farewell tour.

123
00:05:49,880 --> 00:05:51,160
One last thing, popping in to see you,

124
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:53,280
then I'm off to see
the Alignment of Exodor.

125
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:54,680
The Alignment of Exodor?

126
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:57,560
Seventeen galaxies in perfect unison.

127
00:05:57,640 --> 00:05:59,480
Meant to be spectacular.
I can't miss it.

128
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:01,720
Literally can't.
It's locked in a time stasis field.

129
00:06:01,800 --> 00:06:04,760
I get one crack at flying my Tardis
straight into it,

130
00:06:04,840 --> 00:06:06,680
if I get my dates right,

131
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:08,840
-which I have.
-Sounds nice.

132
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:11,880
So this is me, popping in and
popping out again, just being social,

133
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:13,160
just having a laugh.

134
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:16,680
Never mind that.

135
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:19,160
-Never mind what?
-Mmm, nothing.

136
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:20,880
No, you've noticed something. You've...

137
00:06:20,960 --> 00:06:24,240
You've got your noticing face on.
I have nightmares about that face.

138
00:06:24,320 --> 00:06:27,080
Nope. Given all that up.
Done noticing things.

139
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:28,320
Didn't even notice that, for example.

140
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:30,120
Well, got to go. Good seeing you, Craig.

141
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:31,520
Goodbye, Stormageddon.

142
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,040
(BABBLING)

143
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:36,000
No, wait, wait.
Can you do the shushy thing?

144
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:40,640
No, it only works once, and only on
life forms with underdeveloped brains.

145
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:43,040
Hang on! You said "farewell tour”.

146
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:45,400
-What do you mean, farewell...?
-Shh.

147
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:52,040
Just go. Stop noticing. Just go.
Stop noticing. Just go. Stop noticing.

148
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,480
Just go. Stop it.

149
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:54,800
Am I noticing? No.

150
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:56,520
No, I am not.

151
00:06:56,600 --> 00:07:00,320
And what I'm not doing is scanning
around for electrical fluctuations.

152
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:02,280
Oh, shut up, you.
I'm just dropping in on a friend.

153
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:04,600
The last thing I need right now is
a patina of teleport energy.

154
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:06,600
I'm going. Do you hear me? Going.

155
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:10,640
Not staying, going.
I am through saving them.

156
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:13,800
I'm going away now.

157
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:16,160
(TOYS SQUEAKING AND WHIRRING)

158
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:19,360
(IMITATING AEROPLANE SOUND)
It goes up, tiddly-up, it goes down,

159
00:07:19,440 --> 00:07:20,920
diddly-down, for only 49.99,

160
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,760
which I personally think is a bit steep.

161
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:26,280
But then again, it's your parents' cash
and they'll only waste it

162
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:28,520
on boring stuff
like lamps and vegetables.

163
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:29,800
Yawn.

164
00:07:29,880 --> 00:07:32,400
Yeah, Soph. Just enjoy your holiday.

165
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:34,400
Yeah, coping.

166
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:38,240
Nobody panic,
but I appear to be losing control.

167
00:07:38,320 --> 00:07:40,600
-Yeah, love you...
-Oopsy-daisy.

168
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:44,760
Guys, guys. Ladies and gentlemen,
while I deal with this awkward moment,

169
00:07:44,840 --> 00:07:47,800
you go and find your
parents-slash-guardians.

170
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:49,400
Try in lamps.

171
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:51,200
Craig!

172
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:54,120
What the hell are you doing here?

173
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:57,320
Oh, I'm the Doctor.
I work in a shop now. Here to help.

174
00:07:57,400 --> 00:08:01,080
Look, they gave me a badge with my
name on in case I forget who I am.

175
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:03,640
Very thoughtful, as that does happen.

176
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:07,560
You were leaving.
The Alignment of...Exeter.

177
00:08:07,640 --> 00:08:09,520
What about that?
One chance to see it, you said.

178
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:11,320
Well, I was on my way...

179
00:08:11,400 --> 00:08:14,040
Saw a shop, got a job.
You've got to live in the moment!

180
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:16,320
-Craig, mind Yappy!
-What?

181
00:08:16,400 --> 00:08:17,440
Yappy.

182
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:20,560
The robot dog.
Not as much fun as I remember. (LAUGHS)

183
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:22,800
You look awful.

184
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:25,320
(SIGHS) Well, I haven't slept, have I?

185
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:29,240
I still can't stop him crying.
I even tried singing to him last night.

186
00:08:29,320 --> 00:08:32,720
Yeah, he did mention that.
He thought you were crying, too.

187
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:33,840
He didn't get a wink.

188
00:08:33,920 --> 00:08:35,920
Yappy, say goodbye to Craig
and Stormageddon.

189
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:39,240
"Goodbye, Craig!
Goodbye, Stormageddon!”

190
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:43,360
What was that?

191
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:45,280
You're here for a reason, aren't you?

192
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:47,160
You've noticed something
and you're investigating it.

193
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:49,480
And because it's you,
it's going to be dangerous and alien.

194
00:08:49,560 --> 00:08:50,600
It might not be.

195
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:53,080
-Doctor, I live here. I need to know.
-No, you don't.

196
00:08:53,160 --> 00:08:55,000
My baby lives here. My son.

197
00:08:58,200 --> 00:09:00,000
Sheila Clark went missing Tuesday.

198
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:01,640
Hadif Gosh, last seen Friday.

199
00:09:01,720 --> 00:09:03,640
Tom Luka, last seen Sunday.

200
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:11,760
Why is none of this on the front page?

201
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:14,320
Oh, page one has an exclusive on Nina,

202
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:17,040
a local girl who got kicked off
Britain's Got Talent.

203
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:19,640
These people are on pages seven, 19, 22.

204
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:20,760
Because no one's noticed yet.

205
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:22,960
They're far too excited
about Nina's emotional journey,

206
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:25,720
which, in fairness, is quite inspiring.

207
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:29,160
And what else?

208
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:31,120
These funny old power fluctuations,

209
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:33,880
which just happen to coincide
with the disappearances.

210
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:37,120
No, but that's just the council
putting in new cables, isn't it?

211
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:39,680
Oh, yes. That's it.

212
00:09:39,760 --> 00:09:41,920
Mystery solved. Wasting my time.

213
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:44,400
Now, you can go home
and I can go to Exodor.

214
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:46,760
Goodbye. And here's the lift!

215
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:49,080
-It says it's out of order.
-Not any more.

216
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:50,400
See? Here to help.

217
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:52,280
It says, "Danger!"

218
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:54,640
Oh, rubbish. Lifts aren't dangerous.

219
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:56,080
Do I look like I'm stupid?

220
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:57,200
(COOING)

221
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:59,280
(CHUCKLES) Quiet, Stormy.

222
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:04,240
Oh, all right.

223
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:06,240
There's more.

224
00:10:09,040 --> 00:10:11,600
Just between you, me and Stormy,
don't want to frighten the punters,

225
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:14,520
someone's been using a teleport relay
right here in this shop.

226
00:10:14,600 --> 00:10:16,280
Missing people last seen in this area.

227
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:19,000
Before you ask, CCTV's been wiped.

228
00:10:19,280 --> 00:10:20,640
A teleport?

229
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:22,280
A tele... A big...

230
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:25,880
A teleport? Like a beam-me-up

231
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:28,560
-teleport, like you see in Star Trek?
-Exactly.

232
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:32,160
Someone's been using
a beam-me-up Star Trek teleport.

233
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:34,040
Could be disguised as anything.

234
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:37,320
But a teleport in a shop?
That's ridiculous.

235
00:10:37,720 --> 00:10:39,760
What was that?
Was that the lights, again?

236
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:42,760
(HIGH-PITCHED) Yes, that's it.
That's all. It's the lights.

237
00:10:42,840 --> 00:10:43,920
Why'd you say that like that?

238
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,960
Like what? (LOWERS PITCH) Like what?

239
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,400
Like that, in that high-pitched voice.

240
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,880
Just keep looking at me, Craig.
Right at me. Just keep looking.

241
00:10:49,960 --> 00:10:52,080
-Why?
-Well, because, because...

242
00:10:52,160 --> 00:10:53,280
Because I love you.

243
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:55,080
You love me?

244
00:10:55,160 --> 00:10:57,000
Yes, Craig, it's you.
It's always been you.

245
00:10:57,080 --> 00:10:58,120
Me?

246
00:10:58,200 --> 00:11:00,000
Is that so surprising?

247
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:01,480
Doctor, are you going to kiss me?

248
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:02,680
Yes, Craig. Yes, I am.

249
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:04,520
Would you like that?
Bit out of practice,

250
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:06,200
but I've had some wonderful feedback.

251
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:09,120
Doctor, no. I can't. I'm taken!

252
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:10,440
(SCREAMING) Oh, my God!

253
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:12,520
Or we could just hold hands if
it'd make you feel more comfortable.

254
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:13,640
What is happening?

255
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:16,840
Well, first of all, I don't really
love you, except as a friend.

256
00:11:17,240 --> 00:11:18,400
What is that?

257
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:21,160
(YELLING)

258
00:11:25,560 --> 00:11:28,200
-Quick reverse.
-Okay, what the hell just happened?

259
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:29,600
(LIFT BELL DINGS)

260
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:33,120
They must have linked the teleport
relay to the lift, but I've fused it.

261
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,600
They can't use that again.

262
00:11:34,680 --> 00:11:38,240
-Stuck up there on their spaceship.
-What were those things?

263
00:11:40,040 --> 00:11:41,160
Cybermen.

264
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:43,400
A ship?

265
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:44,640
A spaceship?

266
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:46,680
We were in space!

267
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:53,120
It's got to be up there somewhere.
Can't get a fix. It must be shielded.

268
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:55,360
But you fused the teleport.
You sorted it.

269
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:56,480
They can't come back.

270
00:11:56,560 --> 00:11:58,200
No, no, no.
I just bought myself a little time.

271
00:11:58,280 --> 00:12:00,760
I've still got to work out what
they're doing before I can stop it.

272
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:02,520
But if they've got the teleport,

273
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:03,840
and they're that evil,

274
00:12:03,920 --> 00:12:05,320
why haven't they invaded already?

275
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:08,920
Craig, take Alfie and go.

276
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:12,480
No.

277
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,840
-No?
-No.

278
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:18,240
I remember from last time.
People got killed.

279
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:20,200
People that didn't know you.

280
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:22,600
I know where's safest for me and Alfie,

281
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:24,040
-and that's right next to you.
-Is that so?

282
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:26,480
Yeah, you always win.
You always survive.

283
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:31,440
Those were the days.

284
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:32,560
I can help you.

285
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:34,520
I'm staying.

286
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:36,720
Craig...

287
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:39,400
Craig...

288
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:43,320
All right!

289
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:45,800
All right, maybe those days
aren't quite over yet.

290
00:12:46,440 --> 00:12:48,240
Let's go investigate.

291
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:51,080
I mean, there's no immediate danger now.

292
00:12:56,160 --> 00:12:57,720
-Good afternoon, Val.
-Hello.

293
00:13:00,080 --> 00:13:01,240
(CRAIG STUTTERING)

294
00:13:02,040 --> 00:13:03,440
Where am I investigating?

295
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:05,440
Well, look around.

296
00:13:05,520 --> 00:13:08,160
Ask questions.
People like it when you're with a baby.

297
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:10,240
Babies are sweet. People talk to you.

298
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:13,440
That's why I usually take
a human with me.

299
00:13:13,680 --> 00:13:15,840
-So I'm your baby?
-You're my baby.

300
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:18,480
Mmm.

301
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:21,600
Okay.

302
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:28,080
I hope you don't mind my saying, Doctor,
but I think you look ever so sweet.

303
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:30,320
You and your partner and the baby.

304
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:32,960
Partner? Yes, I like it.

305
00:13:33,040 --> 00:13:34,400
Is it better than companion?

306
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:37,520
"Companion.” Sounds old-fashioned.

307
00:13:37,680 --> 00:13:39,760
There's no need to be coy these days.

308
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:42,800
Not noticed anything unusual
around here lately, Val?

309
00:13:42,880 --> 00:13:44,600
-Well...
-Yes, yes?

310
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:47,320
Mary Wornock saw...

311
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:50,920
Don Petheridge snogging Andrea Groom

312
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:54,960
outside the Conservative Club
on his so-called day off golfing.

313
00:13:55,920 --> 00:13:57,160
Yeah?

314
00:13:57,240 --> 00:13:59,280
Maybe this wasn't such a good idea
after all.

315
00:14:01,120 --> 00:14:04,280
And then there's that silver rat thing.

316
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:08,040
What?

317
00:14:14,640 --> 00:14:15,760
(ALFIE COOING)

318
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:19,680
All right, Alfie,
you watch Daddy investigate.

319
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:21,880
You look cute, I'll do the talking.

320
00:14:24,720 --> 00:14:25,880
(BEEPING)

321
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:36,280
Good afternoon, sir. Can I help you?

322
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:38,040
Hiya.

323
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:40,920
-I'm Craig.
-Yeah?

324
00:14:43,200 --> 00:14:45,120
Do you mind if I ask you some questions?

325
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:46,360
You what?

326
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:48,920
Just between me and you, in confidence.

327
00:14:49,400 --> 00:14:51,200
Have you noticed anything

328
00:14:51,960 --> 00:14:53,200
unusual?

329
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:56,280
-Interesting?
-You what?

330
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:59,000
Talk to me about ladies wear.

331
00:14:59,240 --> 00:15:00,280
George!

332
00:15:04,080 --> 00:15:05,520
Hi, George.

333
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:07,920
Nice uniform.

334
00:15:09,040 --> 00:15:10,160
Silver rat...

335
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:15,400
Glowing red eyes.

336
00:15:15,480 --> 00:15:16,640
Yes.

337
00:15:16,760 --> 00:15:18,480
Then it zizzed off.

338
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:20,760
I wanted to get one for my nephew,

339
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:23,080
but stockroom say there's no such item.

340
00:15:23,160 --> 00:15:24,560
Oh, I bet they do.

341
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:26,920
Well, what was it, then? Answer me that.

342
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:29,120
Can I help you, sir?

343
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:32,600
Have you seen how cute my baby is?

344
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:35,600
(LAUGHING) We're going to
head off, actually.

345
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:37,800
All right. Whoa!

346
00:15:38,160 --> 00:15:39,720
What's all that hullabaloo?

347
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:42,440
Um... That'll be my partner.

348
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:44,760
Ah...

349
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:47,480
Make a habit of hanging around
in women swear, sir?

350
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:50,680
-(ALFIE CRYING)
-I'm sorry. Oh, shh, Alfie, come on.

351
00:15:50,760 --> 00:15:52,400
He's a pervert. Look at him.

352
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:53,840
Hello, everyone. Here to help!

353
00:15:53,920 --> 00:15:54,960
-Hello, Doctor.
-Hello, Doctor.

354
00:15:55,040 --> 00:15:58,440
Hello. Has anyone seen a silver rat?

355
00:15:59,360 --> 00:16:01,360
No. Okay, long shot.

356
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:03,640
I see you've met my friend Craig.

357
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:05,720
-Nice uniform, George.
-Hmm.

358
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:07,840
-(WHISTLES)
-Thank you, Doctor.

359
00:16:07,920 --> 00:16:09,680
If he's with you,
that's all right, then.

360
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:11,000
Sorry.

361
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:12,880
I thought he was hassling me

362
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:14,160
'cause that's the last thing
I need today.

363
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:15,560
'Cause Shona's not turned up, right?

364
00:16:15,640 --> 00:16:18,160
So I'm doing twice the work
for the same money, if you don't mind...

365
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:19,280
Shh.

366
00:16:19,360 --> 00:16:23,040
-Please teach me how to do that.
-No. Hold on, un-shh.

367
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:26,480
-Shona?
-My supervisor.

368
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:28,800
She's meant to be in today
but never showed up.

369
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:30,520
Where did you last see her?

370
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:34,000
How'd you do that?

371
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:35,120
It's a power, isn't it?

372
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:37,360
Some sort of weird alien hypnotic power.

373
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:40,720
I bet you excrete some sort of gas
that makes people love you.

374
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:42,200
Would that I could, Craig.

375
00:16:43,200 --> 00:16:45,080
-(WOMAN SCREAMS)
-Ah! Sorry, madam.

376
00:16:45,160 --> 00:16:47,080
I'd try that in red if I were you.

377
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:49,320
-I'm right, though, aren't I?
-Well, you love me.

378
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:52,160
I've never excreted any weird
alien gases at you.

379
00:16:52,240 --> 00:16:53,760
I don't love you.
Don't start that again.

380
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:55,360
(COOING)

381
00:16:55,680 --> 00:16:57,320
Yes, I know. Of course he does.

382
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:59,240
Of course you do. We're partners.

383
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:00,920
Yeah, but I did exactly
what you would've done

384
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:02,320
and I nearly got arrested.

385
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:04,320
(COOING)

386
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:06,400
Stormy thinks you should
believe in yourself more.

387
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:08,320
Great. So now my baby's reviewing me.

388
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:10,600
Here. Right here. Last night.

389
00:17:11,760 --> 00:17:13,520
A Cyberman took Shona.

390
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:17,400
A Cyberman?
I thought it was a little silver rat.

391
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:20,080
It's not a rat.

392
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:21,760
It's a Cybermat.

393
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:25,000
All right. Don't have a go at me
just because I don't know the names.

394
00:17:25,080 --> 00:17:28,200
Cybermats are infiltrators.
Very small, very deadly.

395
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:30,880
They collect power
like bees collect pollen.

396
00:17:30,960 --> 00:17:33,280
One of them has been sucking
the electrical energy from this area.

397
00:17:33,360 --> 00:17:35,120
But why a shop?

398
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:37,520
You know, why not
a nuclear power station?

399
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:39,760
-Okay, why?
-Let's ask it.

400
00:17:39,840 --> 00:17:41,720
We wait for the shop to shut,
we stake the place out,

401
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:43,280
we grab ourselves a Cybermat.

402
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:45,120
And this is just a coincidence, is it?

403
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:47,040
-What is?
-Aliens in Colchester.

404
00:17:47,120 --> 00:17:48,920
Aliens twice in my life,

405
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,920
happening to me just when you turn up.

406
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:52,760
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
this is not my fault, Craig.

407
00:17:52,840 --> 00:17:54,280
Oh, shh, look what you've done now.

408
00:17:54,360 --> 00:17:55,440
It's his nappy. He's mentioned it twice.

409
00:17:55,520 --> 00:17:57,440
Yeah, well, sorry,
I don't speak baby, do I?

410
00:17:57,520 --> 00:18:00,000
There's a changing station
over by Electrical Goods.

411
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:02,520
Of course you'd know that.
Come on, Alfie.

412
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:05,480
Craig! It's a coincidence!

413
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:08,360
It happens,
it's what the universe does for...

414
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:12,240
Can I have your autograph, please?

415
00:18:12,320 --> 00:18:13,600
Uh, yeah, sure.

416
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:15,840
...fun.

417
00:18:15,920 --> 00:18:17,800
AMY: Uh, what's your name?
GIRL: Ellie.

418
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:19,800
"To Ellie."

419
00:18:19,880 --> 00:18:21,680
-I like your hairband.
-Thank you.

420
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:36,520
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

421
00:19:02,080 --> 00:19:03,480
Amelia Pond.

422
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:18,200
Okay, shh.

423
00:19:20,760 --> 00:19:22,320
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER HUMMING)

424
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:23,560
Right.

425
00:19:24,040 --> 00:19:26,040
Let's be having you then, Cybermat.

426
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:27,920
(ALFIE CRYING)

427
00:19:28,120 --> 00:19:29,160
Shh!

428
00:19:29,240 --> 00:19:30,920
Can't you put that on quiet?

429
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:33,280
No. It's a sonic screwdriver.

430
00:19:33,360 --> 00:19:35,080
Sonic equals sound.

431
00:19:35,840 --> 00:19:38,320
Take this.
I got it on my discount, 10% off.

432
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:39,640
It's a papoose.

433
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:41,680
-Why do I need a papoose?
-Alfie wants you attached to him.

434
00:19:41,760 --> 00:19:44,800
You are far too slow
when he summons you.

435
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:47,080
When's he going to stop giving me marks?

436
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:48,800
Never. It's parenthood.

437
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:50,440
Couldn't you have just got a babysitter?

438
00:19:50,520 --> 00:19:53,000
-(ALFIE COOING)
-No, any babysitter.

439
00:19:53,080 --> 00:19:54,240
Doesn't have to be a hot one.

440
00:19:54,320 --> 00:19:55,480
I told everyone I know

441
00:19:55,560 --> 00:19:57,240
-I didn't need their help this weekend.
-Well.

442
00:19:57,320 --> 00:19:58,600
They won't even answer my calls.

443
00:19:58,680 --> 00:20:01,320
I didn't know there was going to be
an invasion of Cybermen.

444
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,520
(SHUSHING)

445
00:20:08,600 --> 00:20:09,720
(BUZZING)

446
00:20:11,360 --> 00:20:13,720
(ALFIE FUSSING, BOTH SHUSHING)

447
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:16,080
-It's okay.
-(RHYTHMIC BEEPING)

448
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:17,520
(GASPS)

449
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:18,640
A-ha!

450
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:20,680
It's very hot.

451
00:20:20,760 --> 00:20:22,160
Must be on low power.

452
00:20:22,240 --> 00:20:25,080
I'm better at that than I remember.

453
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:26,720
(CRAIG PANTING)

454
00:20:27,880 --> 00:20:29,000
-Oh, is that it?
-Yeah.

455
00:20:29,080 --> 00:20:31,200
Oh, that's quite cute. Look at that.

456
00:20:31,360 --> 00:20:33,400
-Look, Alfie, look...
-(BOTH YELL)

457
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:34,840
(CRAIG GASPING)

458
00:20:38,480 --> 00:20:39,920
(CLATTERING)

459
00:20:46,280 --> 00:20:48,720
Metal rat, real mouth!
Metal rat, real mouth!

460
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:50,000
-Yes, I know it is.
-Metal rat...

461
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:52,200
Stop, stop screaming! Shh!

462
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:56,320
(GEORGE SCREAMING)

463
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:57,840
Come on!

464
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:02,040
George!

465
00:21:05,160 --> 00:21:06,960
(ELECTRICITY BUZZING)

466
00:21:09,840 --> 00:21:10,960
George.

467
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:12,080
(GRUNTS)

468
00:21:15,560 --> 00:21:16,640
CRAIG: Doctor!

469
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:18,600
Doctor!

470
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:20,000
Doctor!

471
00:21:20,160 --> 00:21:21,240
What happened?

472
00:21:21,320 --> 00:21:23,160
Oh, I've been chipped...

473
00:21:23,240 --> 00:21:24,320
Chapped...

474
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:25,480
Chopped!

475
00:21:25,560 --> 00:21:27,080
(GRUNTS) The Cyberman.

476
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:29,480
It killed George.
Took him back to the ship.

477
00:21:29,560 --> 00:21:30,800
The Cybermen are here?

478
00:21:30,880 --> 00:21:33,240
-But you said...
-Yeah, I know what I said, okay?

479
00:21:33,320 --> 00:21:35,400
A lot of things.
But I fused the teleport.

480
00:21:35,480 --> 00:21:37,280
It should've taken them days to repair.

481
00:21:37,360 --> 00:21:38,480
Are you okay?

482
00:21:38,560 --> 00:21:41,440
Oh, I should be dead, but the arm
it chopped me with, it was damaged.

483
00:21:41,520 --> 00:21:44,920
Old spare parts. Must have changed
those missing people. (MUMBLES)

484
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:47,440
Changed the missing into Cybermen?

485
00:21:47,800 --> 00:21:49,200
Why didn't they change you?

486
00:21:49,280 --> 00:21:53,720
Long story. I'm not exactly compatible,
but why are they using spare parts?

487
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:56,240
Why? Everything I find out
makes less sense.

488
00:21:56,320 --> 00:21:59,240
Doctor, listen to me. If the Cybermen
are here, then we're not safe.

489
00:21:59,320 --> 00:22:01,840
We've got to go.
We've got to go back to base.

490
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:03,440
We've got a base?

491
00:22:03,520 --> 00:22:04,880
When did we get a base?

492
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:10,480
I'm going down the shop.
We've run out of milk.

493
00:22:10,560 --> 00:22:12,280
You know what to do if he cries.

494
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:14,920
No.

495
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:17,040
-Me, neither!
-(DOOR CLOSES)

496
00:22:17,320 --> 00:22:18,640
(ALFIE CRYING)

497
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:20,920
Oh.

498
00:22:27,840 --> 00:22:29,000
Hello, Stormageddon.

499
00:22:29,280 --> 00:22:30,560
(WHINING)

500
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:32,200
It's the Doctor,

501
00:22:32,720 --> 00:22:33,880
here to help.

502
00:22:34,640 --> 00:22:37,720
Um, shh, shh-shh.

503
00:22:37,800 --> 00:22:40,640
-Hey! There, there.
-(COOING)

504
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:41,800
Be quiet.

505
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:43,880
Go to sleep.

506
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:45,960
(ALFIE FUSSING)

507
00:22:46,040 --> 00:22:47,160
Oh. Really?

508
00:22:47,680 --> 00:22:50,360
Stop crying. You've got a lot
to look forward to, you know.

509
00:22:51,200 --> 00:22:54,040
A normal human life on earth.

510
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:56,680
Mortgage repayments,

511
00:22:56,960 --> 00:23:02,280
the nine-to-five, a persistent,
nagging sense of spiritual emptiness.

512
00:23:02,440 --> 00:23:03,520
(COOING)

513
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:06,120
Save the tears for later, boy-o.

514
00:23:06,640 --> 00:23:09,080
(GRUMBLING) No, that was...

515
00:23:09,160 --> 00:23:10,360
crabby.

516
00:23:10,520 --> 00:23:11,840
No, that was old.

517
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:15,120
But I am old, Stormy.

518
00:23:16,640 --> 00:23:18,240
I am so old.

519
00:23:19,160 --> 00:23:20,360
So near the end.

520
00:23:27,800 --> 00:23:29,120
(BEEPING)

521
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:33,560
You, Alfie Owens,

522
00:23:34,600 --> 00:23:35,720
you

523
00:23:36,480 --> 00:23:37,840
are so young.

524
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:39,880
Aren't you?

525
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:42,320
And you know, right now,

526
00:23:43,080 --> 00:23:45,120
everything's ahead of you.

527
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:47,640
You could be anything.

528
00:23:47,720 --> 00:23:49,240
-(WHINING)
-Yes.

529
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:51,360
I know.

530
00:23:51,640 --> 00:23:53,720
You could walk among the stars.

531
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:55,880
They don't actually look like that,
you know.

532
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:57,800
They are rather more impressive.

533
00:23:59,160 --> 00:24:00,800
(ELECTRONIC BUZZING)

534
00:24:02,920 --> 00:24:04,040
Yeah.

535
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:08,760
You know, when I was little like you,
I dreamt of the stars.

536
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:12,760
I think it's fair to say,
in the language of your age,

537
00:24:12,840 --> 00:24:14,680
that I lived my dream.

538
00:24:15,440 --> 00:24:17,160
I owned the stage.

539
00:24:18,200 --> 00:24:19,760
Gave it 110%.

540
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:25,800
I hope you have as much fun
as I did, Alfie.

541
00:24:27,240 --> 00:24:28,920
(RHYTHMIC BEEPING)

542
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:33,920
Your dad's trying his best, you know.

543
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:35,040
(ALFIE COOING)

544
00:24:35,120 --> 00:24:38,080
Yes, I know. It's not his fault,
he doesn't have mammary glands.

545
00:24:38,160 --> 00:24:39,320
(ALFIE CRIES)

546
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:40,640
No, neither do I.

547
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:43,920
(RHYTHMIC BEEPING)

548
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:45,040
Alfie,

549
00:24:45,120 --> 00:24:47,640
why is there a sinister beeping
coming from behind me?

550
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:53,680
Oh, no, you don't!

551
00:24:54,960 --> 00:24:57,360
Come on, Alfie, run! It's only stunned.

552
00:24:57,920 --> 00:24:59,000
(CRYING)

553
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:01,080
Yes, we're okay. Good, Alfie.

554
00:25:01,160 --> 00:25:02,480
We'll go outside.
Don't worry about it, we'll go outside.

555
00:25:02,560 --> 00:25:03,880
(RHYTHMIC BEEPING)

556
00:25:04,520 --> 00:25:05,640
Yeah, look...

557
00:25:06,320 --> 00:25:07,360
Oops.

558
00:25:12,760 --> 00:25:13,880
I'm back!

559
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:18,840
(VIBRATING)

560
00:25:19,320 --> 00:25:21,480
Come on, Craig, pick up,
pick up, pick up!

561
00:25:21,560 --> 00:25:22,600
Doctor?

562
00:25:24,400 --> 00:25:25,480
(SOFTLY) Doctor?

563
00:25:28,520 --> 00:25:29,680
(RHYTHMIC BEEPING)

564
00:25:33,480 --> 00:25:35,040
(GRUNTING)

565
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:38,000
Craig, don't worry.

566
00:25:38,080 --> 00:25:40,440
Alfie is fine,
but on no account enter the house.

567
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:41,840
Doctor!

568
00:25:43,920 --> 00:25:45,680
No, no, no, no, no, no!

569
00:25:47,720 --> 00:25:48,880
Alfie!

570
00:25:56,840 --> 00:25:58,600
Where's Alfie? Where's Alfie?

571
00:25:58,680 --> 00:26:00,760
-He's safe! He's safe!
-Get it off me!

572
00:26:00,840 --> 00:26:02,720
I just have to find the right frequency
to shut it down.

573
00:26:02,800 --> 00:26:03,960
-Kill it!
-Whoa!

574
00:26:04,560 --> 00:26:06,160
All right, all right, all right, move!

575
00:26:07,600 --> 00:26:08,760
(YELLING)

576
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:12,960
(YELLING) Baking tray, Craig,
baking tray!

577
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:14,800
(BOTH YELLING)

578
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:17,680
-Hold it down.
-Get on with it.

579
00:26:17,760 --> 00:26:20,120
Oh, it must be shielded from
metastatic energy, of course!

580
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:22,200
-Yeah, of course!
-Don't worry, I have an app for that.

581
00:26:22,280 --> 00:26:23,760
Stand back. Stand back!

582
00:26:24,840 --> 00:26:26,240
(ELECTRONIC BUZZING)

583
00:26:30,520 --> 00:26:31,760
Success.

584
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:33,880
That was amazing.

585
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:36,520
You must be really, really strong!

586
00:26:36,600 --> 00:26:37,960
That thing should've had you easily.

587
00:26:38,360 --> 00:26:39,560
It's definitely dead?

588
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:41,560
Inactive, yes.
Technically, never been alive.

589
00:26:41,640 --> 00:26:45,480
It was "playing possum” before
to take us by surprise.

590
00:26:45,840 --> 00:26:46,880
Bravo.

591
00:26:46,960 --> 00:26:48,760
-(CHUCKLES)
-Hey?

592
00:26:49,240 --> 00:26:50,720
(BOTH SIGHING)

593
00:26:51,680 --> 00:26:52,800
(WHOOPING)

594
00:26:53,960 --> 00:26:55,120
Alfie!

595
00:26:57,200 --> 00:26:59,600
(YAWNING) I'm knackered.

596
00:27:00,600 --> 00:27:03,000
That thing was eating up
the electricity?

597
00:27:03,080 --> 00:27:06,240
And transmitting it up to the Cybership.
But why?

598
00:27:06,680 --> 00:27:07,800
And why do they need power?

599
00:27:07,880 --> 00:27:09,520
Why are those conversions
not complete yet?

600
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:10,880
And what are they doing up there?

601
00:27:10,960 --> 00:27:12,600
You said you were going to
look at its brain.

602
00:27:12,800 --> 00:27:13,960
Well, I had to wipe its brain.

603
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:17,040
Now, I can reprogram it,
use it as a weapon against them.

604
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:19,600
The Cybermat came after us.

605
00:27:19,760 --> 00:27:20,800
No, after me.

606
00:27:20,920 --> 00:27:23,320
-They sent it after us.
-After me.

607
00:27:24,520 --> 00:27:26,440
Because of me,
you and Alfie nearly died.

608
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:27,560
(ALFIE COOING)

609
00:27:29,360 --> 00:27:31,280
Do you still feel safe with me, Craig?

610
00:27:31,800 --> 00:27:33,600
(CHUCKLES)
Can't help who your mates are.

611
00:27:33,680 --> 00:27:34,720
No.

612
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:39,080
I am a stupid, selfish man.
Always have been.

613
00:27:40,040 --> 00:27:42,880
I should've made you go.
I should never have come here.

614
00:27:43,800 --> 00:27:45,280
What would've happened
if you hadn't come?

615
00:27:45,360 --> 00:27:48,320
Who else knows about
the Cybermen and teleports?

616
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:50,480
I put people in danger.

617
00:27:50,560 --> 00:27:52,040
Stop beating yourself up.

618
00:27:52,360 --> 00:27:53,480
If it weren't for you,

619
00:27:53,560 --> 00:27:55,640
this whole planet
would be an absolute ruin.

620
00:27:57,680 --> 00:28:00,400
Uh, Craig, very soon I won't be here.

621
00:28:01,520 --> 00:28:04,160
My time is running out.

622
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:06,720
I don't mean Exodor.

623
00:28:07,600 --> 00:28:10,720
"Silence will fall
when the question is asked."

624
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:14,360
I don't even know what the question is.
I always knew I'd die still asking.

625
00:28:15,120 --> 00:28:17,080
The thing is, Craig,

626
00:28:17,680 --> 00:28:19,200
it's tomorrow.

627
00:28:20,880 --> 00:28:22,400
Can't put it off any more.

628
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:25,920
Tomorrow is the day I...

629
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:32,320
(EXHALES)

630
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:40,960
(ALFIE COOING)

631
00:28:46,320 --> 00:28:48,280
(CYBERMAT BEEPING)

632
00:28:49,320 --> 00:28:50,640
Safe mode.

633
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:52,440
Clever me.

634
00:28:53,600 --> 00:28:54,920
Come along, bitey.

635
00:28:55,760 --> 00:28:57,280
SOPHIE: So, I'll be back about 10:00,

636
00:28:57,360 --> 00:28:59,200
because Melina's
totally gone off on one.

637
00:28:59,280 --> 00:29:02,880
She's going to kill David Jenkins.
I know I'm stupid to worry.

638
00:29:02,960 --> 00:29:05,280
-I can't wait to get home...
-No, no, no. Doctor?

639
00:29:05,480 --> 00:29:07,560
Love you, Alfie. Love you, Craig.

640
00:29:07,640 --> 00:29:08,760
(ANSWERING MACHINE BEEPS)

641
00:29:09,040 --> 00:29:10,480
You idiot!

642
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:16,680
-Morning.
-Morning.

643
00:29:16,920 --> 00:29:18,400
Teleport's still fused.
They didn't repair it.

644
00:29:18,480 --> 00:29:20,920
So, the Cyberman last night,
how did it get down here?

645
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:22,360
How did it get out? And why?

646
00:29:22,440 --> 00:29:24,400
Why am I asking you?

647
00:29:24,480 --> 00:29:26,000
You found the silver rat?

648
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:27,560
But where are the silver men?

649
00:29:28,240 --> 00:29:30,840
I'm sorry, Alfie, I can't
leave you here on your own.

650
00:29:30,920 --> 00:29:32,960
There's something up with the Doctor
and we owe him.

651
00:29:33,040 --> 00:29:35,240
I wouldn't have you or Mummy
if it wasn't for him.

652
00:29:35,320 --> 00:29:36,360
(ALFIE GURGLING)

653
00:29:36,840 --> 00:29:37,960
He needs someone.

654
00:29:38,040 --> 00:29:40,240
He always needs someone.
He just can't admit it.

655
00:29:40,320 --> 00:29:42,520
I promise nothing's
going to happen to you.

656
00:29:43,400 --> 00:29:44,800
All right, come on. Here we go.

657
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:47,000
Secondary teleport?
No, there is no other teleport.

658
00:29:47,080 --> 00:29:49,240
They must have had a backup system.

659
00:29:49,440 --> 00:29:50,920
Something complicated.

660
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:53,680
Something powerful. Something shielded.

661
00:29:54,480 --> 00:29:56,160
Something like...

662
00:29:56,480 --> 00:29:58,080
a door? A door.

663
00:29:58,800 --> 00:30:03,440
A dyscillium-bonded steel door,
disguised as a wall.

664
00:30:03,520 --> 00:30:05,400
That is cheating!

665
00:30:08,560 --> 00:30:09,680
So...

666
00:30:10,960 --> 00:30:12,480
they didn't teleport down,

667
00:30:13,360 --> 00:30:14,920
they climbed up.

668
00:30:17,360 --> 00:30:19,440
(SONIC SCREWDRIVER HUMMING)

669
00:30:38,800 --> 00:30:40,600
(ELECTRICITY BUZZING)

670
00:30:54,160 --> 00:30:55,480
(WHISTLES)

671
00:30:58,520 --> 00:31:01,000
Well, well, well. You have been busy.

672
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:05,160
Doctor? Doctor?

673
00:31:05,240 --> 00:31:06,480
Another row?

674
00:31:06,560 --> 00:31:09,320
He went in the changing room.
Something about silver men.

675
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:10,520
Oh, God, no. Val,

676
00:31:10,600 --> 00:31:12,880
I need you to look after Alfie
for me, okay?

677
00:31:12,960 --> 00:31:14,360
Please look after him.

678
00:31:14,440 --> 00:31:16,920
-The Doctor needs me.
-I understand.

679
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:18,800
You two need time alone.

680
00:31:18,880 --> 00:31:20,040
Don't follow me!

681
00:31:20,120 --> 00:31:22,280
I wasn't intending to.

682
00:31:28,720 --> 00:31:29,960
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

683
00:31:33,320 --> 00:31:35,360
You have come to us.

684
00:31:36,080 --> 00:31:37,360
Took me a while.

685
00:31:37,880 --> 00:31:39,120
A lot on my mind.

686
00:31:41,480 --> 00:31:44,640
Let's see. This ship crashed here
centuries ago.

687
00:31:44,720 --> 00:31:47,360
No survivors, but the systems
are dormant, waiting for power,

688
00:31:47,440 --> 00:31:48,720
and then the council

689
00:31:48,800 --> 00:31:51,160
stick a load of new cables
right on top of you.

690
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:53,680
Bitey wakes up and channels the power.

691
00:31:53,760 --> 00:31:55,960
You start crewing up from the shop
as best you can.

692
00:31:56,040 --> 00:31:58,000
Not enough power. Not enough parts.

693
00:31:58,080 --> 00:32:00,400
When we are ready, we will emerge.

694
00:32:00,480 --> 00:32:03,040
We will convert this planet
to Cyber-form.

695
00:32:03,120 --> 00:32:04,160
What, six of you?

696
00:32:04,240 --> 00:32:08,240
You know that is enough.
You know us. You are the Doctor.

697
00:32:08,320 --> 00:32:10,920
Correct. And the Doctor always
gives you a choice.

698
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:13,760
Deactivate yourself or I deactivate you.

699
00:32:20,880 --> 00:32:22,600
Doctor! Doctor!

700
00:32:22,800 --> 00:32:24,160
Oh!

701
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:25,880
(PANTING)

702
00:32:28,080 --> 00:32:29,360
(BEEPING)

703
00:32:30,880 --> 00:32:31,960
(YELLING)

704
00:32:32,040 --> 00:32:34,000
He must be the new leader.

705
00:32:34,080 --> 00:32:36,160
No. He is not like us.

706
00:32:36,240 --> 00:32:39,120
Brain and binary muscular system
incompatible.

707
00:32:39,200 --> 00:32:42,080
They will be discarded,
other body parts may be of use.

708
00:32:42,160 --> 00:32:43,200
Oi!

709
00:32:43,280 --> 00:32:47,080
Cybermen, you get off my planet
or I activate this.

710
00:32:47,160 --> 00:32:49,560
Craig, stop this. Get out!

711
00:32:49,640 --> 00:32:52,200
It's like you said, Doctor,
you got to believe you can do it.

712
00:32:53,160 --> 00:32:54,400
You located us?

713
00:32:54,480 --> 00:32:56,680
Yeah, the teleport in the lift.
A bit rubbish.

714
00:32:56,760 --> 00:32:58,640
And that little Cybermat
never stood a chance.

715
00:32:58,720 --> 00:32:59,760
You see what you're dealing with?

716
00:32:59,840 --> 00:33:02,040
You are compatible. You are intelligent.

717
00:33:02,840 --> 00:33:03,920
(SCREAMING)

718
00:33:05,880 --> 00:33:08,240
No! I'm not intelligent.
You don't want me.

719
00:33:08,320 --> 00:33:11,560
Do not fear.
We will take your fear from you.

720
00:33:11,640 --> 00:33:15,120
You will be like us.
You will be more than us.

721
00:33:16,880 --> 00:33:17,920
No, no, no!

722
00:33:18,080 --> 00:33:20,320
Your designation is Cyber Controller.

723
00:33:20,400 --> 00:33:21,520
-You will lead us.
-No!

724
00:33:21,600 --> 00:33:23,160
We will conquer this world.

725
00:33:23,560 --> 00:33:24,920
-Doctor!
-Craig!

726
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:26,680
-Do something, please!
-(GRUNTS)

727
00:33:29,080 --> 00:33:30,160
Doctor!

728
00:33:30,240 --> 00:33:33,480
Craig, don't worry. I've reprogrammed
their Cybermat. It'll drain their power.

729
00:33:33,560 --> 00:33:34,600
(BEEPS)

730
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:38,880
You have failed, Doctor.

731
00:33:38,960 --> 00:33:43,440
Begin conversion, phase one.
Cleanse the brain of emotions.

732
00:33:43,880 --> 00:33:44,920
No.

733
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:48,000
Craig, fight it. They can't convert you
if you fight back.

734
00:33:48,080 --> 00:33:50,080
-You're strong. Don't give into it.
-Help me!

735
00:33:50,160 --> 00:33:51,880
Think of Sophie. Think of Alfie.

736
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:53,800
Craig, don't let them take it all away.

737
00:33:53,880 --> 00:33:56,480
Make it stop! Please, make it stop!

738
00:33:56,760 --> 00:33:58,440
Please, listen to me. I believe in you.

739
00:33:58,520 --> 00:34:00,680
I believe you can do this.
I've always believed.

740
00:34:00,760 --> 00:34:02,080
In all of you, all my life!

741
00:34:02,160 --> 00:34:03,400
(GROANING)

742
00:34:03,480 --> 00:34:04,960
I'm going to die, Craig.

743
00:34:05,040 --> 00:34:08,560
Tomorrow I'm going to die, but I don't
mind if you just prove me right.

744
00:34:08,920 --> 00:34:10,080
Craig!

745
00:34:16,160 --> 00:34:17,960
Begin full conversion.

746
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:21,880
(ALFIE CRYING)

747
00:34:22,320 --> 00:34:23,480
Don't worry.

748
00:34:25,400 --> 00:34:27,480
It's just a little light going out.

749
00:34:28,240 --> 00:34:29,600
(ALFIE CRYING)

750
00:34:29,680 --> 00:34:31,640
CYBERMAN: Unknown sound wave detected.

751
00:34:32,080 --> 00:34:35,320
It is the sound of fear.
It is irrelevant.

752
00:34:35,400 --> 00:34:37,120
We will remove all fear.

753
00:34:37,800 --> 00:34:39,560
Alfie, I'm so sorry!

754
00:34:41,040 --> 00:34:44,720
Alfie, please, stop. I can't help him.

755
00:34:45,560 --> 00:34:48,640
Emotions eradicated.
Conversion complete.

756
00:34:48,720 --> 00:34:50,680
(ALFIE CONTINUES CRYING)

757
00:34:54,400 --> 00:34:55,920
(ALARM BLARING)

758
00:34:57,240 --> 00:35:00,440
Alert. Emotional subsystems rebooting.

759
00:35:00,520 --> 00:35:02,240
This is impossible.

760
00:35:02,480 --> 00:35:05,960
He can hear him. He can hear Alfie.

761
00:35:06,240 --> 00:35:08,840
Oh, please, just give me this.

762
00:35:09,040 --> 00:35:11,320
Craig, you wanted a chance
to prove you're a dad,

763
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:13,400
you are never going to get
a better one than this.

764
00:35:14,360 --> 00:35:15,600
What is happening?

765
00:35:15,680 --> 00:35:19,160
What's happening, you metal moron,
a baby is crying

766
00:35:19,440 --> 00:35:21,520
and you'd better watch out
because guess what?

767
00:35:21,760 --> 00:35:24,360
(LAUGHS) Daddy's coming home!

768
00:35:25,400 --> 00:35:26,560
Alfie!

769
00:35:27,160 --> 00:35:28,240
(LAUGHING)

770
00:35:28,600 --> 00:35:32,000
Alfie, I'm here! I'm coming for you!

771
00:35:32,080 --> 00:35:34,240
Guess what? It stopped.

772
00:35:34,320 --> 00:35:35,360
Alfie!

773
00:35:35,720 --> 00:35:36,760
(CRYING)

774
00:35:37,400 --> 00:35:38,480
Alfie needs you!

775
00:35:38,560 --> 00:35:41,200
Emergency! Emotional influx.

776
00:35:41,280 --> 00:35:44,200
You've triggered a feedback loop
into their emotional inhibitors.

777
00:35:44,280 --> 00:35:45,560
(CYBERMEN GRUNTING)

778
00:35:45,640 --> 00:35:48,440
All that stuff they cut out of
themselves, now they're feeling it.

779
00:35:49,800 --> 00:35:51,720
Which means a very big explosion.

780
00:35:51,800 --> 00:35:54,480
Overload! Overload! Overload!

781
00:35:54,720 --> 00:35:57,480
-Get out! We need to get out!
-Ah! They've sealed the ship.

782
00:35:57,880 --> 00:35:59,760
-We've got to get out of here!
-I know!

783
00:36:00,800 --> 00:36:02,040
The teleport!

784
00:36:04,400 --> 00:36:05,560
(ELECTRONIC BUZZING)

785
00:36:05,640 --> 00:36:06,680
(BOTH EXCLAIM)

786
00:36:14,760 --> 00:36:16,360
(LIFT BELL DINGS)

787
00:36:17,080 --> 00:36:19,120
-How did you get in there?
-Alfie!

788
00:36:19,960 --> 00:36:21,600
Here's your daddy.

789
00:36:21,680 --> 00:36:22,800
(ALFIE GIGGLING)

790
00:36:22,880 --> 00:36:24,960
That was another review, 10 out of 10.

791
00:36:25,440 --> 00:36:27,680
The Cybermen, they blew up.

792
00:36:28,320 --> 00:36:30,400
I blew 'em up with love.

793
00:36:30,480 --> 00:36:32,520
No, that's impossible.

794
00:36:32,600 --> 00:36:35,520
And also, grossly sentimental
and oversimplistic.

795
00:36:35,600 --> 00:36:37,360
You destroyed them
because of the deeply ingrained

796
00:36:37,440 --> 00:36:39,840
hereditary human trait
to protect one's own genes.

797
00:36:39,920 --> 00:36:43,400
Which, in turn, triggered a...a...a...

798
00:36:45,320 --> 00:36:47,360
Yeah. Love.

799
00:36:49,200 --> 00:36:50,880
You blew them up with love.

800
00:36:54,280 --> 00:36:57,760
The building should be totally safe,
structurally, and of course,

801
00:36:57,840 --> 00:37:00,840
the bonded dyscillium
contained the explosion.

802
00:37:01,120 --> 00:37:03,800
Right. Why are you telling me all this?

803
00:37:03,880 --> 00:37:05,640
I don't know. Shh.

804
00:37:06,800 --> 00:37:08,680
-It suits you.
-Thanks.

805
00:37:08,760 --> 00:37:11,480
-Discount applies to partners.
-Great!

806
00:37:11,800 --> 00:37:13,240
Are you two married, then?

807
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:17,400
No. No, we talked about it, but
it's just a piece of paper, isn't it?

808
00:37:17,480 --> 00:37:20,400
Thank you for your help, Val.
Good noticing, keep 'em peeled.

809
00:37:20,480 --> 00:37:23,960
I will. I'm glad you two made up,
for baby's sake.

810
00:37:24,040 --> 00:37:25,080
Aw.

811
00:37:26,440 --> 00:37:27,480
How do you mean?

812
00:37:27,560 --> 00:37:31,240
It's nice for baby to have two daddies
who love each other.

813
00:37:31,920 --> 00:37:34,360
Wait. (LAUGHING) Hang on a sec.

814
00:37:35,120 --> 00:37:37,080
Two daddies? You think that I'm...

815
00:37:37,160 --> 00:37:39,120
-His companion.
-(LAUGHS)

816
00:37:40,320 --> 00:37:41,600
Doctor...

817
00:37:42,440 --> 00:37:45,080
VAL: Gone. Now where's he rushed off to?

818
00:37:49,800 --> 00:37:50,840
He's gone.

819
00:37:58,480 --> 00:37:59,840
Who's tidied all this up?

820
00:38:13,400 --> 00:38:14,440
(CHUCKLES)

821
00:38:20,560 --> 00:38:22,120
See? I do come back.

822
00:38:23,240 --> 00:38:24,880
-How did you...
-Time machine.

823
00:38:24,960 --> 00:38:29,280
But even with time travel,
getting glaziers on a Sunday,

824
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:30,920
tricky.

825
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:33,960
You went back in time,
that means you used up your hours.

826
00:38:34,040 --> 00:38:35,200
What about Exodor?

827
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:37,360
What about you being in trouble
with Sophie when she comes back?

828
00:38:37,440 --> 00:38:38,600
I couldn't let that happen.

829
00:38:39,160 --> 00:38:40,560
You used up your time for me?

830
00:38:40,640 --> 00:38:42,120
Course I did, you're me mate.

831
00:38:42,280 --> 00:38:45,240
I notice Stormageddon"s
very quiet and happy.

832
00:38:45,320 --> 00:38:46,360
(GIGGLES)

833
00:38:46,440 --> 00:38:48,280
Oh, he prefers the name Alfie now.

834
00:38:48,360 --> 00:38:49,400
(COOING)

835
00:38:49,480 --> 00:38:52,080
And he's very proud of his dad.

836
00:38:52,160 --> 00:38:55,160
-He calls me Dad?
-Yes, of course he does now.

837
00:38:55,240 --> 00:38:56,280
(GURGLING)

838
00:38:56,520 --> 00:38:58,320
Yeah, I know, he's a bit thick,
isn't he?

839
00:38:58,400 --> 00:39:00,440
(LAUGHING) Oi, shut up, you two.

840
00:39:01,160 --> 00:39:02,400
Well...

841
00:39:02,800 --> 00:39:05,680
Now it's time. I have to go.

842
00:39:06,800 --> 00:39:09,200
Doctor, I know that something's wrong.
I can help you.

843
00:39:09,280 --> 00:39:10,560
Nobody can help me.

844
00:39:11,600 --> 00:39:14,840
Um, I hope Sophie won't mind,
I need these.

845
00:39:15,560 --> 00:39:18,160
-Where are you going to go?
-America.

846
00:39:19,240 --> 00:39:21,440
Sophie will be home any second,
are you sure...

847
00:39:21,520 --> 00:39:23,520
I can't miss this appointment, Craig.

848
00:39:25,360 --> 00:39:26,400
Goodbye, mate.

849
00:39:27,720 --> 00:39:29,640
Wait there. One second.

850
00:39:36,120 --> 00:39:37,520
From Sean's dad.

851
00:39:39,640 --> 00:39:41,760
-Wow.
-You ride 'em, partner.

852
00:39:41,840 --> 00:39:43,200
Oh, thanks!

853
00:39:49,200 --> 00:39:50,280
Bye.

854
00:39:50,360 --> 00:39:51,480
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

855
00:39:51,560 --> 00:39:53,240
Doctor, that'll be Sophie...

856
00:39:58,360 --> 00:39:59,680
(KNOCKING)

857
00:40:02,800 --> 00:40:04,360
Hello, hello. I forgot my key.

858
00:40:04,440 --> 00:40:06,120
Oh, I missed you so much.

859
00:40:06,200 --> 00:40:08,480
I missed you, too. Both of you.

860
00:40:09,080 --> 00:40:10,400
Are you wearing a papoose?

861
00:40:10,640 --> 00:40:11,720
Yeah, it's...

862
00:40:15,320 --> 00:40:17,760
Oh, my God. The place is spotless.

863
00:40:18,360 --> 00:40:19,760
Has something happened?
You look different.

864
00:40:20,040 --> 00:40:21,960
Nothing happened. Nothing weird.

865
00:40:22,400 --> 00:40:25,320
Look at you two, thick as thieves.

866
00:40:25,400 --> 00:40:27,000
Who's Daddy's little boy, then?

867
00:40:27,080 --> 00:40:28,120
ALFIE: Doctor Who.

868
00:40:28,200 --> 00:40:29,320
What?

869
00:40:29,680 --> 00:40:30,840
Craig?

870
00:40:38,680 --> 00:40:40,240
Well, then, old girl.

871
00:40:43,600 --> 00:40:45,280
One last trip, eh?

872
00:40:55,960 --> 00:40:57,040
Hey.

873
00:40:57,960 --> 00:40:59,040
I'm the Doctor.

874
00:41:00,800 --> 00:41:02,080
I was here to help.

875
00:41:03,800 --> 00:41:05,520
And you are very, very welcome.

876
00:41:12,160 --> 00:41:16,080
It was funny, he seemed so happy
but so sad at the same time.

877
00:41:17,080 --> 00:41:21,000
I was just a kid, I thought maybe he
was a cowboy on his way to a gunfight.

878
00:41:21,720 --> 00:41:23,640
I really liked his hat.

879
00:41:35,560 --> 00:41:38,200
MADAME KOVARIAN:
Tick-tock goes the clock,

880
00:41:38,440 --> 00:41:41,240
and what now shall we play?

881
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:45,200
Tick-tock goes the clock,

882
00:41:46,680 --> 00:41:49,480
now summer's gone away.

883
00:41:49,680 --> 00:41:50,880
Hello?

884
00:41:52,000 --> 00:41:54,360
Such a lovely old song.

885
00:41:55,040 --> 00:41:56,680
But is it about him?

886
00:41:58,560 --> 00:42:01,920
-You know about the Doctor?
-So very well.

887
00:42:02,560 --> 00:42:05,480
Oh, don't try and remember me.

888
00:42:05,840 --> 00:42:10,400
We've been far too thorough
with your dear little head.

889
00:42:14,720 --> 00:42:15,920
(GASPS)

890
00:42:16,760 --> 00:42:19,280
What are they? What are those things?

891
00:42:19,560 --> 00:42:21,640
-Your owners.
-My what?

892
00:42:21,720 --> 00:42:24,560
So they made you a Doctor today,
did they?

893
00:42:25,920 --> 00:42:28,320
Dr River Song.

894
00:42:29,160 --> 00:42:30,880
How clever you are.

895
00:42:32,560 --> 00:42:36,120
You understand what this is, don't you?

896
00:42:36,480 --> 00:42:40,160
According to some accounts,
it's the day the Doctor dies.

897
00:42:40,520 --> 00:42:45,200
"By Silencio Lake,
on the Plain of Sighs

898
00:42:45,800 --> 00:42:49,280
"an Impossible Astronaut will rise
from the deep

899
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:54,120
"and strike the Time Lord dead.”

900
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:57,440
It's a story.

901
00:42:59,120 --> 00:43:02,400
And this is where it begins.

902
00:43:02,480 --> 00:43:04,280
(DOOR BUZZES OPEN)

903
00:43:08,120 --> 00:43:11,520
You never really escaped us,
Melody Pond.

904
00:43:12,280 --> 00:43:14,400
We were always coming for you.

905
00:43:14,480 --> 00:43:17,640
-How do you know who I am?
-I made you what you are.

906
00:43:18,360 --> 00:43:22,160
The woman who kills the Doctor.

907
00:43:22,400 --> 00:43:25,560
(YELLING) No! No! No! Oh!

908
00:43:27,400 --> 00:43:28,720
(GASPING)

909
00:43:30,720 --> 00:43:35,760
Tick-tock goes the clock,
and all the years they fly.

910
00:43:36,800 --> 00:43:39,760
Tick-tock, and all too soon,

911
00:43:40,080 --> 00:43:43,560
your love will surely die.

912
00:43:54,800 --> 00:43:58,560
CHILDREN: # Tick-tock goes the clock

913
00:43:58,640 --> 00:44:02,680
# The cradle man, he rocked her

914
00:44:02,760 --> 00:44:06,560
# Tick-tock goes the clock

915
00:44:06,640 --> 00:44:10,120
# Till River kills the Doctor #

916
00:44:12,320 --> 00:44:15,440
Before I go, I'd like to know
why I have to die.

917
00:44:16,480 --> 00:44:18,960
Silence will fall
when the question is asked.

918
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:22,360
All the times I've heard those words,

919
00:44:22,440 --> 00:44:25,560
I never realised it was my silence,
my death.

920
00:44:27,720 --> 00:44:28,760
(SCREECHING)

921
00:44:34,040 --> 00:44:35,160
It's time.

